==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[advertize]]

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[avertir]]'', formerly also spelt ''[[advertir]]'', to warn, give notice to, {{L.}} ''[[advertere]]'' to turn to.  The ending was probably influenced by the noun [[advertisement]].  See [[Advert]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæd.vɚ.taɪz/

===Transitive Verb===
{{en-verb|advertis|ing}}

# To give public notice of; to announce publicly, as, to advertise goods for sale, a lost article, the sailing day of a vessel, a political meeting.

====Synonyms====
To [[promote]]; [[apprise]]; [[inform]]; make known; [[notify]]; [[announce]]; [[proclaim]]; [[promulgate]]; [[publish]].

